# AhaDiff

Use this Codex agent skill when a code change should be learned back from the
diff instead of explained from memory.

## Commands

- `ahadiff learn HEAD~1..HEAD` captures the latest commit.
- `ahadiff learn --staged` captures staged changes before commit.
- `ahadiff quiz <run_id>` reviews generated quiz questions.
- `ahadiff review` opens the due SRS queue backed by `review.sqlite`.
- `ahadiff verify <run_id>` rechecks claims and score artifacts.
- `ahadiff improve <run_id>` proposes targeted improvements for weak evidence.
- `ahadiff serve` opens the local WebUI for runs, lessons, review, and graphs.

## Local State

- `.ahadiff/review.sqlite` is the local review and SRS truth source.
- `.ahadiff/runs/<run_id>/` stores run artifacts such as claims, lessons,
  quizzes, scores, and provenance.
- `prompts/` contains the prompt templates that shape generated learning output.

Prefer AhaDiff artifacts with verified claims and file-line evidence over
free-form summaries. Keep provider credentials in environment variables and do
not commit private audit logs.
